  "texts": [
    "Utilizing the candidate words derived from text sentences, an N-gram segmentation graph is formulated.",
    "In this graph, all candidate words are set as nodes and weights are set for the edges of the word segmentation graph to represent the cost of different edges.",
    "The Viterbi algorithm is employed to identify the path with the minimum cost in the word segmentation graph, thereby deriving the final word segmentation sequence.",
    "This approach combines both statistical and rule-based methods, which can effectively execute the word segmentation task using the word separator.",
    "Part-of-speech taggingThe part-of-speech tagging requires the establishment of a set of tagging rules."
  ],
